  },
  "items": [
    {
      "kind": "title",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "O Uso de \"am, is, are\" na História da Criação",
      "file": "pt-br-7e3816f1db5fc7e3afe7fbcc3309bcf55e47dcc0.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Introdução",
      "file": "pt-br-94977e20e93eb4bff6542a7fff4c92dba1e736e6.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Olá, pessoal! Hoje vamos aprender sobre três palavras muito importantes em inglês: \"am\", \"is\" e \"are\". Essas palavras fazem parte do verbo \"to be\" no presente e são usadas para descrever identidade, características e estados.",
      "file": "pt-br-90c3b14ba7985e6eb4a338ffb0e50d4dc8fa853a.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "O que são \"am\", \"is\" e \"are\"",
      "file": "pt-br-6cfd7bb65c73d68bd9a086455ff2f28d8efdf26e.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "O verbo \"to be\" no presente pode aparecer de três formas diferentes, dependendo do sujeito da frase. Vamos ver cada uma delas:",
      "file": "pt-br-11ad46fda6a801ba680198dd9ad0776229835ddd.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "am",
      "file": "en-us-9e56dbeff632a968c7f64f17c36f33091ce42857.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Usamos \"am\" apenas com \"I\" (eu).",
      "file": "pt-br-d37abc06a340484ad49a1398df47c398cdeb8946.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "I am happy.",
      "file": "en-us-23939b7341e0b2db15f437958c508b0842216b70.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eu estou feliz.",
      "file": "pt-br-4240ee01934ed8d8f4697259d5f69ec8b887ac59.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "is",
      "file": "en-us-0e9663d7d581d51c921feac4e349804643900d59.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Usamos \"is\" com \"he\", \"she\" e \"it\" (ele, ela e isso).",
      "file": "pt-br-d4174307d9e0b096c85d4096fd68eec51fd84c26.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "He is tall.",
      "file": "en-us-af163ec42bea51f3309be7bba94b099b8c63c975.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Ele é alto.",
      "file": "pt-br-1c27c85f5f4c372ee6ab23bcfa20532332b374e8.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "She is kind.",
      "file": "en-us-019c1e9cf13b9e9edd13907ed0c10a28ab5691a6.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Ela é gentil.",
      "file": "pt-br-6a727df98525db2edc3ac36dcb20547049c5cc94.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "It is small.",
      "file": "en-us-8f98a3230c224cbd3f93f0122c851d912157f6ab.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Isso é pequeno.",
      "file": "pt-br-e1f946f04ab10bb1c8421c2a19539c7dbfc5d59f.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "are",
      "file": "en-us-f7adbfc3092900b98273949b64a73d0067f5ce1a.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Usamos \"are\" com \"we\", \"you\" e \"they\" (nós, você/vocês e eles/elas).",
      "file": "pt-br-f17a20c53c2b57fc7a475003092ed7fb373bf0bd.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "We are friends.",
      "file": "en-us-f85a438612ea85b5533543e702c91062a54aebb6.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Nós somos amigos.",
      "file": "pt-br-bc581a00d4584a6dbe0b6aff41754b94b5fc857a.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "You are important.",
      "file": "en-us-52a2fa8d7ca09e3d5e568b8181df5b0a2619ec73.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Você é importante.",
      "file": "pt-br-b989ad67418b29804ab6629f60cb7d58d9038c8e.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "They are strong.",
      "file": "en-us-cfdd0e2875449009f23b7ce631553918fc40c121.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eles são fortes.",
      "file": "pt-br-dc6d5c488c7d5cf734a16b078b404aa86fa1465f.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Frases afirmativas",
      "file": "pt-br-500debcaf830948bdec9a391f8f2d0ca02db2d2d.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Na forma afirmativa, usamos apenas o verbo.",
      "file": "pt-br-63487ac064961a69171359b4883b12da7f1534f1.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "God is good.",
      "file": "en-us-11ee17c9157ed0472cd61cd5fbf248d89b38edd3.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Deus é bom.",
      "file": "pt-br-bf9fdbeed0af54042a45eab4376425fc49c72301.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "We are in the world.",
      "file": "en-us-73a7100fade0219249e864ed48cc69aabe4296cc.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Nós estamos no mundo.",
      "file": "pt-br-b18104ebba4c4d892ee42eb899f7696f6a9cd24f.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Frases negativas",
      "file": "pt-br-f8aff7cfd6eb45f35c0263854279bdea478a2a94.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Na forma negativa, usamos \"not\".",
      "file": "pt-br-5ec620ef5389f96322287b5f5715d780bad6d14b.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "It is not dark.",
      "file": "en-us-4bf230af42ce5f9aea76d38c684ccd5c930a827c.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Não está escuro.",
      "file": "pt-br-673e92f6e9b60bca8e1fd7650a72d3a89a407820.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "They are not alone.",
      "file": "en-us-55977a0c313b4bd0abd39c0a0ac6a29317820792.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eles não estão sozinhos.",
      "file": "pt-br-36051a67075a78ed3f810c1e25e994f3bbd7f0fa.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Contrações em inglês",
      "file": "pt-br-769d687e49caa7b9eccad16fd9acbf46ff2f1da3.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "No inglês falado, usamos formas mais curtas para deixar a fala natural. Essas formas são chamadas de contrações.",
      "file": "pt-br-d832ca9752aa10ec27ac8b080f7ac523e088d81a.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "I am = I'm",
      "file": "en-us-3551d31347d0ad0dc6f190977bd6ac041e78b193.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Exemplo:",
      "file": "pt-br-1f257340c6973475b77762f1f48d0bab701485d4.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "I'm happy.",
      "file": "en-us-1f6a5fb43cd019673e73d7131a98641197a01145.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eu estou feliz.",
      "file": "pt-br-4240ee01934ed8d8f4697259d5f69ec8b887ac59.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "He is = He's",
      "file": "en-us-b273b8301973f38254d51f1afb6e01a1701abaff.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Exemplo:",
      "file": "pt-br-1f257340c6973475b77762f1f48d0bab701485d4.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "He's strong.",
      "file": "en-us-7cac01ef3493237e3ffd7fce80c7394626aeeeb9.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Ele é forte.",
      "file": "pt-br-1ea8706bd241e03d1c9bc0800fa0e1a2e1d29b43.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "They are = They're",
      "file": "en-us-8f94e65dda1e009000679f0c8f6a657ebd425219.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Exemplo:",
      "file": "pt-br-1f257340c6973475b77762f1f48d0bab701485d4.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "They're here.",
      "file": "en-us-312f716fb2ccf7dd87290e79cb359f8381528440.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eles estão aqui.",
      "file": "pt-br-768d8d5192cab588c5e82e1c368e110439ef4083.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Essas contrações são muito usadas no dia a dia e tornam o inglês mais fluido e natural.",
      "file": "pt-br-6004901f322ca05f0e0cb3a0b331b72177468966.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Expressões úteis: \"That’s\", \"There’s\" e \"Here’s\"",
      "file": "pt-br-dcb41c597a853bc1374146b98035490854db25d8.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Além das formas contraídas de \"am\", \"is\" e \"are\", existem três expressões muito comuns que ajudam a tornar a fala mais natural.",
      "file": "pt-br-bdaaca0576a6a6f3313d439755abbd762fb9c9db.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "That’s = That is",
      "file": "en-us-fb0028a02294b19456c93e21870aec2050934be5.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Essa é a criação de Deus.",
      "file": "pt-br-d72262a322afb7d42353add939881a5f92cddfbe.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "That’s God’s creation!",
      "file": "en-us-0333666b8a3d6c6e07024abe4354124f8ece8b03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "There’s = There is",
      "file": "en-us-67b470f0f332183a55d241edf38fab26cd3bba34.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Agora há luz no mundo.",
      "file": "pt-br-5abde68ce1b8d46fc1f7603dda78a159c4adaf88.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "There’s light in the world now!",
      "file": "en-us-38ce9a7e80cac37ef28a68558b7ddc9f314db7b3.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "Here’s = Here is",
      "file": "en-us-d048fbe169e2253c719c31212931f30f225041dd.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Aqui está o céu que Deus criou.",
      "file": "pt-br-03704575502f7513d0c60dea6237dabb6941ac23.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "Here’s the sky God made!",
      "file": "en-us-f4c87e39df9ca5070e71fc25094e4a138f71cab1.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Exemplos na História da Criação",
      "file": "pt-br-f61b156ba563537deef56b1238ac6aaa153428c6.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Agora, vamos ver como essas palavras aparecem em frases sobre a criação do mundo.",
      "file": "pt-br-9f6d283482d132d437f51e7ba0bdb8f3565d135c.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "I am Hannah. I am happy to tell you this story.",
      "file": "en-us-9542a0ba207decd1a2c01f1bd49ca878559d61e7.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Eu sou Hannah. Estou feliz em contar esta história para você.",
      "file": "pt-br-331ef4ac06adbbf6fe505c4d252f19b5f9eb7bf5.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "The sky is blue. The stars are bright.",
      "file": "en-us-5e5dcdee8806b65597d4e3c244790b72a6941a51.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "O céu é azul. As estrelas são brilhantes.",
      "file": "pt-br-1b4a8dbfa0b2a4c33e78db6a00978e4b7d8c86f5.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "God is the Creator. God is good.",
      "file": "en-us-9f77eeffc8a0e522ac299b9aa5a749116d8a4770.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Deus é o Criador. Deus é bom.",
      "file": "pt-br-fa3139ec54142f1fc982a7124cc20b8f35e2e2b0.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "That’s how the world began!",
      "file": "en-us-cdc65930162a591e3e7bf0aad7bc1c6d9c6c1e3b.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Foi assim que o mundo começou.",
      "file": "pt-br-fa07d97e88b8741525f40284cc6c077d52d8ebc0.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "There’s a beautiful garden.",
      "file": "en-us-08dacfa2d037e475090eccc35f86ae8ec5e83471.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Há um belo jardim.",
      "file": "pt-br-8094b6ef5e1ead8971e1974cc78c80f327299250.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text-bold-large",
      "lang": "en-US",
      "voice": "en-US-Standard-I",
      "text": "Here’s the sun that shines brightly.",
      "file": "en-us-5d9143e6fbd7bb5d61cae4c165cf538b567d1408.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Aqui está o sol que brilha intensamente.",
      "file": "pt-br-65d0a2a316ca29205173e66817a59e2ef4822957.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "subtitle",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Conclusão",
      "file": "pt-br-daf7ec7b0e18b12d8314fb1593e1fa8534234b86.mp3"
    },
    {
      "kind": "text",
      "lang": "pt-BR",
      "voice": "pt-BR-Standard-C",
      "text": "Hoje aprendemos sobre \"am\", \"is\" e \"are\" e como usá-los em frases. Vimos também como fazer frases negativas e usar contrações. Agora, você já pode usar essas palavras para falar sobre a criação do mundo e muito mais. Até a próxima aula!",
      "file": "pt-br-4abe96e4c8a08ec2905d4974f409f25e59b97045.mp3"
    }
  ]
}